      {
        "content": "Price oracle uses spot reserves enabling flash-loan manipulation\n\nLending market prices collateral from a Uniswap V2 pair's spot reserves (getReserves) instead of a TWAP. An attacker flash-loans, skews the pool, borrows against inflated collateral, and repays \u2014 extracting value. This is an external-call/oracle dependency bug: the contract trusts an externally controllable price source. Fix: use a manipulation-resistant TWAP or Chainlink feed with staleness checks.",
        "doc_id": "code4rena-oracle-spot-price-manipulation",
        "chunk_id": 0,
